tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE SocialMediaEngagementMetrics (
    post_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    likes INT,
    comments INT,
    shares INT,
    engagement_rate FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE social_media_engagement_metrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    platform VARCHAR(255),
    post_id VARCHAR(255),
    likes INT,
    comments INT,
    shares INT
);

CREATE TABLE influencer_impact (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    influencer_id INT,
    brand_id INT,
    engagement_rate FLOAT,
    impact_score INT,
    post_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE Social_Media_Engagement_Metrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    platform VARCHAR(255),
    post_date DATE,
    likes INT,
    comments INT,
    shares INT
);

CREATE TABLE Influencers (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255),
    followers_count INT,
    engagement_rate FLOAT,
    brand_collaborations INT
);

CREATE TABLE Brand_Awareness (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    brand_name VARCHAR(255),
    total_engagement INT,
    influencer_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (influencer_id) REFERENCES Influencers(id)
);

CREATE TABLE social_media_engagement_metrics (
    post_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    post_date DATE,
    post_content TEXT,
    likes INT,
    comments INT
);

CREATE TABLE campaign_metrics (
    campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    campaign_name VARCHAR(50),
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE,
    total_likes INT,
    total_comments INT
);

CREATE TABLE social_media_metrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    post_id INT,
    likes INT,
    shares INT,
    comments INT
);

CREATE TABLE influencers (
    influencer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    followers INT,
    engagement_rate FLOAT,
    category VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE engagements (
    engagement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    influencer_id INT,
    brand_id INT,
    post_id INT,
    engagement_type VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE analytics (
    analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    brand_id INT,
    engagement_id INT,
    analysis_date DATE,
    metrics VARCHAR(100)
);
